org.biohipi.imagebundle

Class BioHipiImageBundle.BioHibReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.biohipi.imagebundle.BioHipiImageBundle.BioHibReader
  • Enclosing class:
    BioHipiImageBundle

    public static class BioHipiImageBundle.BioHibReader
extends Object
    This FileReader enables reading individual images from a BioHipiImageBundle and delivers them in the specified image type. This class is used by the BioHibInputFormat and BioHibRecordReader classes.

      • BioHibReader

        public BioHibReader(org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileSystem fs,
                    org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path path,
                    long start,
                    long end)
             throws IOException
        Creates a BioHibReader to read records (image headers / image bodies) from a contiguous segment (file split) of a BioHIB data file. The segment is specified by a start and end byte offset.
        Parameters:
        fs - The FileSystem where the BioHIB data file resides
        path - The Path to the BioHIB data file
        start - The byte offset to beginning of segment
        end - The byte offset to end of segment
        Throws:
        IOException

      • nextKeyValue

        public boolean nextKeyValue()
        Reads the next image header and image body into memory. To obtain the corresponding BioHipiImageHeader and RasterImage objects, call getCurrentKey() and getCurrentValue() respectively.
        Returns:
        true if the next image record (header + pixel data) was successfully read and decoded. False if there are no more images or if an error occurs.
